title: Green Wing
description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

title: Aspirations
description: The Gangreen Gang is actually committing brilliant crimes. But behind every great gang, there has to be a great woman.

title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
description: When Princess Morbucks tries to ruin Christmas for the children of the world, the Powerpuff Girls must save the day.

title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
description: When Princess Morbucks tries to ruin Christmas for the children of the world, the Powerpuff Girls must save the day.

title: A Made Up Story
description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

title: Snow Month
description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

title: West in Pieces
description: It's the old west and Mojo the Kid has robbed the first bank ever and forced the sheriff out of town and it is up to the Steamypuff Girls to save the day at a high-noon showdown.

title: Escape from Monster Island
description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

title: The Gift
description: The girls must replace the Professor's Christmas present on Christmas Eve.

title: Super Sweet 6
description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

title: Buttercup vs. Math
description: When Buttercup tests into Honors Math, she tries to avoid being labeled a nerd.

title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

title: Clawdad
description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

title: Bye Bye, Bellum
description: The Mayor becomes dependent on the Powerpuff Girls after his assistant Ms. Bellum departs, leaving the girls so busy they accidentally hire the dangerous Bianca Bikini as his new assistant! When Bianca captures the Powerpuff Girls, the Mayor finds the tables turned and must rely on himself to help them.

title: That's Not My Baby/Simian Says
description: That's Not My Baby!: The girls save a baby from a monster attacking Townsville but can't find the mother. Can these three superheroes manage to take care of one little baby?/Simian Says: When the Narrator is mysteriously bound and gagged, Mojo Jojo takes over his job, ordering the girls to steal for him all around Townsville.

title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

title: The Last Donnycorn
description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

title: Splitsville
description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

title: Tiara Trouble
description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

title: The Powerpuff Girls Movie
description: Blossom, Bubbles, and Buttercup--better known as the Powerpuff Girls--reveal the story of how they came to be the official protectors of the City of Townsville. When Professor Utonium first cooked up the Girls in his laboratory, he wasn't trying to give them superpowers. But when the Professor's mischievous monkey lab assistant Jojo knocked a dose of Chemical X into the mix, the Powerpuff Girls were born. While they have such powers as laser beam eyes, superhuman strength and the ability to fly at the speed of light, the Girls are only in Kindergarten. Although they don't mean to hurt anyone, their natural playfulness, coupled with their unnatural abilities, leads to some not-so-natural disasters and earns them the hatred of every man, woman and child in the city of Townsville. The girls are despondent, believing that their powers are evil and nobody loves them. Then Jojo slinks back onto the scene--but the Chemical X-plosion has mutated him into the evil genius Mojo Jojo. He convinces the Girls that he understands the pain of being an outsider, and lets them in on a plan that will endear them to all the people of Townsville--they will build a Help-the-Town-and-Make-it-a-Better-Place-Machine. The Girls immediately set to work gathering the necessary materials from all over the world. But what the Girls don't know is that Mojo Jojo has no intention of making Townsville a better place. In fact, he's planning on using the machine for his own nefarious purposes. Will the Girls realize the truth about Mojo as well as the true potential of their powers in time to really help the town and make it a better place?

title: 15 Minutes of Fame
description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

title: A Star is Blossom
description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

title: Little Miss Interprets/Night Mayor
description: Little Miss Interprets: When the girls hear the Professor trying to make something out of sugar, spice and everything nice, they are sure he's trying to create new little girls./Night Mayor: The Mayor keeps having the same dream over and over again but he never sees the end. Now, it's up the girls to go into the Mayor's head and solve this mystery.

title: Home, Sweet Homesick
description: When the Girls go to Camp, Blossom has a hard time leaving her schoolwork at home.

title: Sun Scream/City of Frownsville
description: Sun Scream: The girls get the ultimate sunburn and must try to fight crime despite their UV damage./The City of Frownsville: When the tearful Lou Gubrious sets a crying ray on Townsville, the girls must find a way to stop the tears before the town is flooded.
